ğŸ” How It Works (RAG Flow)

ğŸ“„ PDF is split into paragraphs (chunks)

ğŸ§  Each chunk is embedded via OpenAI

ğŸ—ƒï¸ Stored in Pinecone with metadata

ğŸ™‹â€â™‚ï¸ User's question is embedded

ğŸ” Pinecone returns top-matching chunks

ğŸ¤– GPT-3.5 is prompted with these chunks

âœ… Response is based ONLY on matched content

ğŸ§ª Sample Backend Code (RAG Pipeline)

const embedding = await openai.embeddings.create({
  model: 'text-embedding-3-small',
  input: userQuestion,
});

const results = await pinecone.index('cybersecvectordb')
  .namespace('ns1')
  .query({
    vector: embedding.data[0].embedding,
    topK: 5,
    includeMetadata: true,
  });

const context = results.matches.map(m => m.metadata.text).join('\n');

const completion = await openai.chat.completions.create({
  model: 'gpt-3.5-turbo',
  messages: [
    { role: 'system', content: 'You are a compliance assistant. Use ONLY the provided context.' },
    { role: 'user', content: `Context:\n${context}\n\nQuestion: ${userQuestion}` },
  ],
});

